{"DISPACE":[{"def":"In this fair plot dispacing to and fro.","pos":""}],"DISPAIR":[{"def":"To separate (a pair).","pos":""}],"DISPAND":[{"def":"To spread out; to expand.","pos":""}],"DISPANSION":[{"def":"Act of dispanding, or state of being dispanded.","pos":""}],"DISPARADISED":[{"def":"Removed from paradise.","pos":""}],"DISPARAGE":[{"def":"To match unequally; to degrade or dishonor by an unequal marriage.","pos":""},{"def":"To dishonor by a comparison with what is inferior; to lower in rank or estimation by actions or words; to speak slightingly of; to depreciate; to undervalue.","pos":""}],"DISPARAGEMENT":[{"def":"Matching any one in marriage under his or her degree; injurious union with something of inferior excellence; a lowering in rank or estimation.","pos":""},{"def":"Injurious comparison with an inferior; a depreciating or dishonoring opinion or insinuation; diminution of value; dishonor; indignity; reproach; disgrace; detraction; -- commonly with to.","pos":""}],"DISPARAGER":[{"def":"One who disparages or dishonors; one who vilifies or disgraces.","pos":""}],"DISPARAGINGLY":[{"def":"In a manner to disparage or dishonor; slightingly.","pos":""}],"DISPARATE":[{"def":"Pertaining to two coördinate species or divisions.","pos":""}],"DISPARATES":[{"def":"Things so unequal or unlike that they can not be compared with each other.","pos":""}],"DISPARITION":[{"def":"Act of disappearing; disappearance.","pos":""}],"DISPARITY":[{"def":"Inequality; difference in age, rank, condition, or excellence; dissimilitude; -- followed by between, in, of, as to, etc.","pos":""}],"DISPARK":[{"def":"To throw (a park or inclosure); to treat (a private park) as a common.","pos":""},{"def":"To set at large; to release from inclosure.","pos":""}],"DISPARKLE":[{"def":"To scatter abroad.","pos":""}],"DISPART":[{"def":"To part asunder; to divide; to separate; to sever; to rend; to rive or split; as, disparted air; disparted towers.","pos":""}],"DISPASSION":[{"def":"Freedom from passion; an undisturbed state; apathy.","pos":""}],"DISPASSIONATE":[{"def":"Free from passion; not warped, prejudiced, swerved, or carried away by passion or feeling; judicial; calm; composed.","pos":""},{"def":"Not dictated by passion; not proceeding from temper or bias; impartial; as, dispassionate proceedings; a dispassionate view.","pos":""}],"DISPASSIONED":[{"def":"Free from passion; dispassionate.","pos":""}],"DISPATCH":[{"def":"To dispose of speedily, as business; to execute quickly; to make a speedy end of; to finish; to perform.","pos":""},{"def":"To rid; to free.","pos":""}],"DISPATCHER":[{"def":"One who dispatches.","pos":""}],"DISPATCHFUL":[{"def":"Bent on haste; intent on speedy execution of business or any task; indicating haste; quick; as, dispatchful looks.","pos":""}],"DISPATCHMENT":[{"def":"The act of dispatching.","pos":""}],"DISPATHY":[{"def":"Lack of sympathy; want of passion; apathy.","pos":""}],"DISPAUPER":[{"def":"To deprive of the claim of a pauper to public support; to deprive of the privilege of suing in forma pauperis.","pos":""}],"DISPAUPERIZE":[{"def":"To free a state of pauperism, or from paupers.","pos":""}]}